        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 1:25PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 124 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Holly, or 15 miles southwest of Coolidge, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holly.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
